Yale tutor, Andover theology, Columbia Law","body":"After Yale 1846 he tutored at Yale 1849-1853, studied theology at Andover Seminary then Yale Divinity, before taking his LL.B. at Columbia Law in 1861 under his cousin Professor Theodore W. Dwight — founder of Columbia Law School. He practiced law in New York City and assisted Theodore at Columbia teaching Municipal Law from 1863 to 1866."},{"number":2,"category":"family","header":"Only child born and died same day, London","body":"He married Cora Charlesina Tallmadge of New York in Philadelphia on 6 June 1866 at age forty. Their only child James McLaren Dwight was born — and died — on 4 May 1872 in London during the couple's extended European travels of 1869-1876."},{"number":3,"category":"death","header":"Tripped in dressing room, died five days later","body":"On the evening of 23 June 1897 he tripped and fell in his dressing room, breaking a thigh. The shock to his seventy-one-year-old system was such that he failed rapidly and died five days later on 1 July, just shy of his seventy-second birthday."}],"quotes":[],"sources":[],"research_sources":[],"documents":[],"slug":"james-dwight-1825"},"HD04881":{"id":"HD04881","former_ids":[],"is_placeholder":false,"has_descendants_documented":false,"bio":{"first_name":"James","middle_name":"McLaren","last_name":"Dwight","married_names":[],"gender":"male","display_name":"James McLaren Dwight (infant)"},"birth":{"year":1872,"month":5,"day":4,"city":"London","county":"City of London","state":"Greater London","country":"England"},"baptism":{},"death":{"year":1872,"month":5,"day":4,"city":"London","county":"City of London","state":"Greater London","country":"England"},"burial":{"cemetery_id":"CEM009","plot_notes":"Grove Street Cemetery, New Haven CT — body returned across Atlantic for burial in father's family plot"},"classification":{"is_thomas_descendant":true,"is_talcott_descendant":false,"is_thomas_spouse":false,"is_talcott_spouse":false,"generation_from_thomas":9,"include